##Cooking for the whole country, fake orgy?

Micro-signal, Rancaijing

A feature presentation, a daily in depth report, redefines the innovation economy.

Original by ran CAIJING

Author | Yu Fan

Editor | Wei Jia

An epidemic has forced people all over the country to learn how to make cool skin.

Things also start with the fact that takeout is not allowed in the community. Everyone learned to calculate the economic accounts during the epidemic: to get a takeout, one needs to consume a mask, one needs to use disposable gloves, and one needs to wash his hands, his hair and his coat, to be perfectly safe, you might as well cook at home.

On the popularity of the topic "staying at home food talent contest" on Weibo

Source / Weibo

For a while, a spontaneous competition called "stay-at-home food talent contest" , from short video platform, cookbook APP to friends' circle, Weibo, the whole network of food lovers contest items from Liangpi to Youtiao, the latest favorite is the rice cooker cake. I know that many people choose to work from home and start to study cooking skills, but I did not expect that some of the players have been challenging the hard model.

The first industry to be affected by the outbreak was the catering industry, which closed almost all restaurants across the country overnight and in some areas even issued emergency notices banning all restaurants from operating. Although many catering enterprises strengthened their take-out business during the extraordinary period, most small areas were closed to take-out, and the whole people responded by "going out less" . In addition, a small number of people were worried about the safety of take-out food, cooking at home seems to be the only solution to the problem of eating.

"during the epidemic, most people had more time and developed the habit of cooking at home, " said Li Zhujie, founding partner of beushuo venture capital. "fresh food is just in demand, and many companies on the track are experiencing a blowout period. " Even Sinopec has started selling vegetables at its gas stations, and convenience, fast food, semi-finished and finished dishes are booming.

Behind the "all-you-can-cook" debate, in addition to a surprise test for fresh food e-commerce, there has also been a series of knock-on effects: Cookbook apps have been among the most popular mobile APPS, and some APP traffic has doubled, sales of convenience food increased 3.5 times, frozen food increased 241 percent year-on-year, and sales of condiments and semi-finished products rose 129 percent and 142 percent respectively on jd.com, and entrepreneurs moving smart cookers from South Korea to the states..

What are the real opportunities behind these phenomena, and what are just short-lived "stress reactions" ?

There's been a spike in the traffic to cookbook APPS

To keep the user, you have to build the product

"I used to cook instant noodles at most, but now I'm forced to cook on the APP, and now I'm openly cooking on my friends' circle, even fantasizing about a self-developed recipe, " Cheng Yu, who works in Beijing, told Rencai, there are only a handful of shops on the delivery platform, he lives in a tightly managed community, the family mask has been desperate, after eating several instant noodles, painful, began to learn to cook.

Do-it-yourself, ample food and clothing, during the epidemic, like Cheng Yu, such as the last-minute study of the recipe of the people are not in the minority.

According to the January 2020 list of mobile APPS, four of the top 20 apps in the food and beverage category were APPS.

Cookbook Sharing Platform "online kitchen" background data shows that during the Spring Festival, the third-and fourth-tier cities have a significant increase in new users. According to CEO  Yang Yang, the outbreak is directly related to the large number of migrant workers stranded in third, and fourth tier cities.

In the big data of the New Year's Eve dinner, sliced chicken with mushrooms, steamed perch and cranberry fat cake were the three dishes that were made the most frequently, with the first two being quick-cooked dishes, Zhong Feng, COO of the food community, told Caijing.

According to Zhong Feng's summary, the reason why the younger generation does not cook is that, in addition to being busy with work and having limited time, most of them grew up at home with their parents cooking and could not cook themselves. During this epidemic, their free time became more and more, many people find it easy to follow a cookbook, and cooking meets the social needs of some young people.

Living in Wenzhou, Song Qi, is commonly known as the circle of friends drying cooking demon.

"after being forced to stay at home for about five days, I started to open the cookbook APP to learn how to cook, because the longest time I spent each day was on news related to the epidemic, which required a diversion of attention to regulate my mood. Cooking was really healing and I could eat what I wanted. " Song Qi's experience is, if participate in the competition, must challenge the difficulty of the recipe, interactive rate will be high.

Song Qi's circle of friends

Source / interviewee

With this dividend, douguo gourmet will be free of charge from January 27. Zhong Feng admitted that in the outbreak of the first time, the team urgent communication, the bean and fruit food can not like a giant to come up with hundreds of millions of dollars in donations, then all the courses free, to support the people at home cooking. Paid courses and e-commerce are the two main ways of cashing out. As of press time, the website has not resumed charging for free courses.

Wang Yuxiang, of the CEO  , told the Financial Times that during the outbreak, people stayed at home behind closed doors and did have a certain bonus for learning to cook. Since the outbreak began, the platform's traffic growth bonus has been obvious, and the increase in traffic has doubled.

Regarding the new users, the feedback from the douguo gourmet backstage is that the new users are similar to the previous user group, mainly women aged 23-45 years old; the emergence of the epidemic has also allowed some male users to join, and the growth rate of male users in Jiangsu, Zhejiang and Shanghai is higher.

That's consistent with the online kitchen's background data. Between January 24 and February 8,20.29 percent of the new users of the online kitchen were female users in third-and fourth-tier cities between the ages of 18 and 34. During this period, Guangdong was by far the most active user of the APP, whether on iOS or Android, next is Zhejiang, Jiangsu, Shanghai, Beijing and other places.

So after the outbreak, these users can stay, users at home cooking habit can continue for how long? Zhong said the outbreak is a catalyst for cookbook apps, raising awareness of the importance of healthy eating and encouraging some people to cook at home.

In the long run, Zhong Feng believes that eating out and eating at home does not conflict, simple meals can be made, complex dishes can be eaten out, and even can be copied at home. Recently, the most popular bean and fruit station recipes, Liang Pi, fried dough sticks, brown sugar fa Gao, are all replica cuisine, and such replica cuisine is often the response of the whole network. Around February 12, the popularity of rice cooker cakes in the bean and fruit station began to soar. CAIREN found that the timing coincided with a trend in the popularity of the same topic on Weibo.

The popularity of the topic of "Rice cooker cake" on Weibo

Source / finance

Zhong Feng thinks the reason behind the electric rice cooker cake's popularity is similar to that of the cold skin. "The ratio of users in the North and south of Douguo station is 1:1. On the fourth day of the Lunar New Year, technical colleagues reported that the search for Liangpi remained high. We were also surprised to find that not only users in the north but also users in the south were involved in the search. " According to Zhong Feng and colleagues, at that time, everyone's New Year's stock is almost consumed, all people at home need to pass the time, cooling process is complex, the operation process is very time-consuming, and on food, tools do not require high, can also share.

Song Qi entered the contest after the topic of the hand-made Liangpi contest in the circle of friends became popular on Weibo. In her words, to make a Liangpi, it would take at least one afternoon. The most important thing is that Liangpi has very low requirements for materials. As long as the family has flour, they can enter the contest, the side dish is also rich and thrifty by people.

Cheng Yu told Caijing that he might cut down on eating out after the epidemic ended because he now finds it easy to cook at home and saves money, "As the online joke says, this epidemic has made many company bosses realize that they can live without many employees. ".

"The outbreak gives recipe software free time, but it's also a critical time to test each product, " an industry insider told CNNMONEY. Users will compare which products work best, only good enough, only then will the user's usage habit continue after the epidemic situation, the user can really remain down.

Yang Yang told CNNMONEY that the outbreak had no impact on the company's long term growth, and that the Internet kitchen's plan was to attract new customers during the outbreak.

Instant noodles and frozen food are snapped up

But only frozen food has a chance of turning over a new leaf

An epidemic forced out a number of cooking army, but also let many people recognize their ability to survive.

Out of concern about their cooking, Cheng Yu returned to Beijing, the first time from home platform snapped up instant noodles, quick-frozen dumplings, hot pot base material. To cut down on the amount of time you spend out of the House, stock up on what you can store, he says.

It's no exaggeration to say that during the outbreak, "which flavor of instant noodles was left in the supermarket near your home? " Has Been Trending on social media. When people are talking about what's wrong with the leftover instant noodles, some people don't have a choice. Lindo, who has a supermarket and a convenience store right at his door, found after reworking that not only did convenience store freezers and rice balls, which have a short shelf life, go out of stock, even the instant noodles and quick-frozen dumplings on supermarket shelves and fresh e-commerce platforms have been snapped up.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Instant noodles and quick-frozen dumplings were snapped up in the supermarket

Source / interviewees

One interesting phenomenon on the Douguo site was the 103 per cent increase in the number of entries for instant noodles and frozen dumplings during the outbreak.

Online sales of these foods have also grown significantly. From New Year's Eve to the ninth day of the Lunar New Year (compared to the same period last year) , the transaction value of convenience food in the whole station increased by 3.5 times, according to JD.com data, multi-platform home orders, fast-food frozen 241% year-on-year growth, especially fast-food, frozen and self-heating food brand orders compared to the same period last year during the Spring Festival 42%-99% growth.

Convenience and frozen food, which have been beaten by takeout, are sought after during the Spring Festival?

Li Heng, the founder of Xiaoheng dumplings, told Caijing that he was part of an army of instant noodles buyers -- as if he'd bought 10 boxes from supermarkets and e commerce platforms on the second day of the Lunar New Year. However, he admitted that the shortage of quick-frozen and convenience food products was a temporary situation due to the shortage of some materials affected by the epidemic, and the situation of supply exceeding demand in the market may not continue until factories resume work and logistics resume.

A few days ago, uni-president publicly said that 80 percent of factories across the country have resumed work, mainly producing instant noodles and beverage products, but due to problems such as the return of personnel, individual factories have not yet been full line production.

"while there is an opportunity for frozen food, this is an opportunity for the entire frozen and retail industry to upgrade their consumption, as well as for some of the food and beverage categories, " Li Heng said, and can do frozen food, such as hot pot base, mutton slices, and so on. In his view, frozen food and retail products are an opportunity for restaurants affected by the outbreak when most people do not eat out; the current boom in fresh food is essentially an upgrade of the frozen and retail industry, as long as the product is done well enough, it is even expected to encroach on the share of traditional enterprises.

Under Li Heng's plan, Xiaoheng will sell 50 percent of its frozen products to fresh e-commerce and e-commerce by 2020. In the first year, retail sales are expected to account for 20 percent to 30 percent of Xiaoheng's total revenues, the ideal ratio for the future is 5:5.

Li Heng believes that the future of the restaurant industry, must be a combination of stores and retail. "This model has been tested in some countries, but the development of the domestic catering industry is slow. This outbreak will push many restaurant owners to change, or promote cooperation or even integration between the catering and frozen retail industries. For example, if the frozen and retail brands want to be restaurant-like, or if the catering enterprises want to be retail-like, then cross-border cooperation is needed. "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Dumpling King General store

Source / network

The popular Japanese restaurant chain Wang Jiang Jiaozi (Jiaozi and Wang Jiang) takes the "catering + retail" route. According to Li Heng, the brand has more than 800 stores in Japan and its retail products are focused on overseas markets such as Hong Kong, Macau and Singapore.

Sales of semi-finished products and condiments rose

It's probably just a false boom

The epidemic hit, the catering industry in the sales season suffered a cold winter, many well-known brands in their own door to do a "vegetable" business, but there is a crisis, some catering enterprises on the front line to introduce semi-finished food ingredients, but good sales.

JD.com, daily fresh and other platforms and off-line restaurant brand cooperation, to develop standard dishes, semi-ready-to-eat production. Jd Online "Restaurant Retail Development Alliance" , including Haidilao, small south, Xibei naked face village, Guangzhou restaurant, more than 100 catering enterprises sales of semi-finished food materials. In JD.com, sales of semi-processed vegetables have risen by more than 142 per cent since January 18, the week before New Year's Eve, while sales of convenience vegetables have risen by 141 per cent year on year. Daily Excellent fresh partner and CFO Wang Jun revealed that in cross-border cooperation with traditional restaurants, in addition to ensuring the daily supply of excellent fresh and semi-finished dishes, the main focus is still on the development of convenience dishes and lazy dishes, this is based on a period of time in the future, the user is not convenient to the offline restaurant to eat, not convenient to order takeout judgment.

Multipoint Dall has also spotted the opportunity, and officials told CNNMONEY that home cooking will remain mainstream until at least the end of March, with multipoint launching fresh food and beverage standards in response to consumer demand and dining habits, such as mushroom rape, pepper potatoes and so on.

Song and Qi also came into contact with semi-finished food materials during the Spring Festival, "there is no time to continue the whole process of buying, washing and chopping vegetables after returning to work [ working from home ] , " she told Caijing. "semi-finished dishes don't even need to think about how much to put in the condiments. Lazy people need them. ".

In the case of food and take-out food being blocked, the whole channel market of semi-finished fast food has become a stop-loss mode for the catering enterprises at this stage. Well, after this epidemic, the semi-finished products provided by the catering enterprises have reached more customers, will you take this opportunity to continue to develop some pre-packaged products as a way to combat risk? After the epidemic, fresh e-commerce platform can also defend the "basket of vegetables" ?

Wu Xiao, an employee in the catering industry, told finance and economics that the current growth in sales of semi-finished food is due to the suspension of in-hall and take-out food, which makes it difficult for consumers to make complex dishes that are close to restaurants, and the demand for semi-finished food will naturally increase, when everything recovered, demand fell back.

The view catering primary school initiator, ruixing business consultant Wang Jie's attitude is also not optimistic. In her view, many restaurant brands during the Spring Festival sales of fresh and semi-finished dishes, the essence of the action is inventory, which in the early stages of the epidemic is a supplement to business, will not become the norm.

"To say the least, even if some catering enterprises have opened up this direction, there will not be too many, because the value of catering is still in the cooking part, and selling clean dishes and semi-finished dishes is already done by a lot of fresh e-commerce, and catering enterprises do not necessarily have the advantages of these platforms, " said Wang Jie.

Condiments were also among the more visible gains in the JD.com data. Since January 18,2020(the week before New Year's Eve) , the turnover of condiments on JD.com platform has increased by more than 129% , with pickles / preserved mustard tuber, soy sauce / Oyster Sauce and hotpot condiments accounting for the highest proportion.

CNFC contacted the relevant person in charge of Xinhe Group and received feedback from CNFC. According to the sales data of TMALL and the stores on the JD.com platform, there was a significant increase in year-on-year post-holiday figures. Visitors to the flagship store of the e-commerce platform exceeded 30% in the same period, the number of sales orders is double that of the same period. But the growth is more affected by the epidemic, due to offline restrictions to online purchase behavior, e-commerce platform conversion rate is also many times higher than usual.

Wu is also inclined to think that the rise in sales of condiments on e-commerce platforms is more due to the shift of consumers'buying channels to the online market in the special period of the epidemic. Overall, he believes the condiment market is still more affected by the development of the catering industry, the current epidemic during almost all restaurants closed, condiment sales overall than in previous years only decreased.

Zao Zuo Co founder Fang Zhong did find a business opportunity.

She had found a smart cooking machine in South Korea, and the team decided there was more room for it at home, so they moved in the same way, and it was launched on a small scale years ago.

The smart cooking machine features one-on-one, which means it needs to be paired with a standardised meal developed by the authorities. According to finance, unlike convenience store meals that are cooked or semi-finished, the smart Cook's meals are also in the form of a box, but raw food, and the machine will automatically cook them when the user pays for them with a Swipe Code.

"The cost of the machine can be reduced to a very low level, " Zhong told CAIJING. "It will then be sold in the form of how many sets of food items the user has bought and sent to the machine. The price for a single meal is around 20 yuan. " The stove does not sell hardware, the core is profiting from the meal.

As the epidemic spread, "When large companies start work one after another, the core demand is to reduce the number of people gathering, or even to avoid too much contact between people. Our project can solve the problem of employees eating while meeting this requirement, " Zhong said, for now, though, the team is focused on the To B business, and the product for C end users is already in development, but production won't start until the factory resumes.

For this business model, Wu said, as a food, take-out supplement is OK, but will not have too much market space. "THE TO B scenario might work, but it's hard To imagine the end-user having a machine in their home and taking turns eating hundreds of dishes, " he says, it's going to be a trend, but it's only going to be for convenience stores and some restaurants, not for C end users to have at home.

Pexels

"How long can people continue to cook at home after the epidemic is over? " CAIJING asked three investors on the issue.

Yan Yan, chief partner of Saifu Investment Fund, said this is a sociological problem. He believes that one of the characteristics of people is that memory is very short-lived and hard to change. If the younger generation is used to ordering takeout, might not change their habits because of an outbreak.

Zhu Xiaohu, managing partner of Jinsha River Venture Capital, said people are lazy by nature and it is difficult to maintain the habit of cooking at home. After the epidemic, people may cook at home a little more than before, but many people will revert to the habit of ordering takeout or takeout.

"It's not sustainable for everyone to be cooped up at home cooking for a long time during the epidemic, and that part of the demand is bound to drop after the epidemic is over. " But Li Zhujie still thinks "eating at home" is a very big track. In fact, bEZUOVENTURE has been looking for companies to innovate on this track.

* The question map was provided by the interviewees. At the request of the interviewees, Cheng Yu, Song Qi, Wu Xiao were given pseudonyms.
